objects.name: AA23-061A #StopRansomware: BlackSuit (Royal) Ransomware
objects.description:
This CSA is being released to notify network defenders of the rebrand from \u201cRoyal\u201d ransomware actors to \u201cBlackSuit,\u201d and include new TTPs, IOCs, and detection methods related to newly branded BlackSuit (formerly known as Royal) Ransomware.

Note: This advisory, originally published March 2, 2023, has been updated twice:

- November 13, 2023: The advisory was updated to share new Royal TTPs and IOCs.

- August 7, 2024: The advisory was updated to notify network defenders of the rebrand of \u201cRoyal\u201d ransomware actors to \u201cBlackSuit.\u201d The update includes new TTPs, IOCs, and detection methods related to BlackSuit ransomware. \u201cRoyal\u201d was updated to \u201cBlackSuit\u201d throughout unless referring to legacy Royal activity. Updates and new content are noted.

(New August 7, 2024) The Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) and the Cybersecurity and Infrastructure Security Agency (CISA) are releasing this joint advisory to disseminate known BlackSuit ransomware IOCs and TTPs identified through FBI threat response activities and third-party reporting as recently as of July 2024.
